{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17637256","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17637256"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T18:41:09+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T18:41:09+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17647"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17647","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17647"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10361"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71776"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10361","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10361"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17647"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57265"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"4948"},{"type":"tags","id":"7748"},{"type":"tags","id":"7828"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24226"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24235"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71776","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/71776"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA researcher compares mean daily caffeine consumption between two groups of university students. The results show:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003EGroup A (n=100): 285 mg/day (95% CI: 260-310)\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EGroup B (n=100): 350 mg/day (95% CI: 325-375)\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the interpretation of these confidence intervals?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["The groups have significantly different caffeine intake","The intervals represent the full range of observed values","The true population means must lie at the centre of each interval","95% of individual measurements fall within these ranges","The difference between groups could be due to chance"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ESince the confidence intervals do not overlap (Group A: 260-310 mg/day vs Group B: 325-375 mg/day), we can conclude that the \u003Cstrong\u003Egroups have significantly different caffeine intake\u003C/strong\u003E at p\u0026lt;0.05.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA 95% confidence interval represents the range within which we can be 95% confident the true population parameter lies. When confidence intervals do not overlap, this indicates a statistically significant difference between groups.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect interpretations are:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E95% of individual measurements fall within these ranges\u003C/strong\u003E - This describes a prediction interval, not a confidence interval. A prediction interval estimates where future individual observations are likely to fall, while a confidence interval estimates the population mean. Individual measurements typically show much more variation than the confidence interval for the mean.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe difference between groups could be due to chance\u003C/strong\u003E - Non-overlapping confidence intervals indicate the difference is statistically significant\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe true population means must lie at the centre of each interval\u003C/strong\u003E - The true mean could lie anywhere within the interval\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe intervals represent the full range of observed values\u003C/strong\u003E - Confidence intervals estimate population parameters, not sample ranges.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["A 95% confidence interval indicates the range within which we can be 95% confident the true population parameter lies.","Confidence intervals that do not overlap between groups indicate a statistically significant difference at p\u003C0.05.","Wider confidence intervals indicate less precise estimates of the population parameter.","Confidence intervals are different from prediction intervals, which estimate the range of individual values"],"references":["Sullivan LM. Essentials of biostatistics in public health. 3rd ed. Burlington (MA): Jones \u0026 Bartlett Learning; 2018.","Dawson B, Trapp RG. Basic \u0026 clinical biostatistics. 4th ed. New York: McGraw-Hill; 2004."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57265"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17647"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57265","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/57265"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-20T15:34:53+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-20T15:36:04+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10361"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71776"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"m